      "text": "A case can be made for locating the starting point of video art with the genesis of television, including [[Ernie Kovacs]]'s 1952 experiments with distorting the signal, or, for the distribution of its origins, to a variety of European and American figures and movements, but if one person is given credit, it is usually the Korean-American artist and musician Nam June Paik."
