    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1ed81305287a0f34",
      "text": "Coming to video as an avant-garde musician, under the influence of John Cage, George Maciunas, and the Fluxus Group, he saw television with its lowbrow reputation as the perfect material pour épater le bourgeois. He first used television sets as altered ready-mades and, in The Moon is the Oldest TV and other works, as [[Self-Referential Machines]] capable of generating images from their own mechanisms-part of the then-current, modernist rhetoric about making work about itself. His experiments with feedback paralleled the art world's interest in process and materials."
